measurementMethod: we measured body length of pinned specimens from head to metasoma end using graph paper
measurementRemarks: We measured one to five individuals, proportionally to how many specimens we collected in the field. For each species, whenever possible, we measured at least one female and one male. We then calculated the mean body size value for each species.

measurementRemarks: We obtained measures of female species specific ITDs from Sydenham et al. (2015) and from specimens in our collected material. We supplemented the ITD measures using specimens from the Natural History Museum in Oslo, Norway, to obtain a mean of minimum five specimens per species. The ITD was rounded to the nearest mm to account for the intraspecific variation in sizes.
